17 (A) An institution of the University System of Georgia; or
18 (B) A unit of the Technical College System of Georgia.
19 (b) No public school, local education agency, or postsecondary institution shall promote,
20 support, or maintain any programs or activities that advocate for diversity, equity, and
21 inclusion beyond upholding the equal protection of the laws guaranteed by the Fourteenth
22 Amendment to the United States Constitution and Article I, Section I, Paragraph II of the
23 Georgia Constitution.
24 (c) Any postsecondary institution that violates subsection (b) of this Code section shall be
25 subject to the withholding of state funding or state administered federal funding. Such
26 withholding of state funding or state administered federal funding shall include funds
27 provided to the postsecondary institution directly as well as funding for scholarships, loans,
28 and grants pursuant to Chapter 3 of this title for students of such postsecondary institution."
29 SECTION 2.
30 This Act shall become effective on July 1, 2025, and shall apply beginning with the
31 2025-2026 school year.
32 SECTION 3.
33 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
